==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: A cheval
<hw>A` che*val"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[F., lit., on
horseback.]</ety> <def>Astride; with a part on each side; -- used
specif. in designating the position of an army with the wings separated
by some line of demarcation, as a river or road.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A position <qex>⟦agrave⟧ cheval</qex> on a river is not one which
a general willingly assumes.</q> <rj><qau>Swinton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>achievability</ent>⟦br⟧
